## 2. Classification scheme

<!-- guidance: The 4-tier default below. If inheriting a policy, replace the
definitions with the policy's verbatim and renumber. Each category in §3 is
assigned EXACTLY ONE class — the highest that applies to any field it can carry
(high-water-mark; "when in doubt, classify up"). -->

| Class | Definition | Default handling posture |
|---|---|---|
| **Public** | Deliberately published; no confidentiality expectation. | Share freely; integrity-protect only. |
| **Internal** | Non-public operational/technical info; mild harm if disclosed. | Need-to-know within the company. |
| **Confidential** | Sensitive business/security data; material harm if disclosed — all customer business data that is not personal data, plus secrets/credentials. | Strict need-to-know; encrypted in transit + at rest; access logged. |
| **Restricted (Customer-PII)** | Personal data of identifiable individuals (org users + CRM contacts); the regulated subset carved out of Confidential. | Everything for Confidential **plus** minimization, redaction on export, breach-handling. |

{{SCHEME_NOTES}}
